## 0. Charter

**Meta-thesis (one sentence):** the exact account is not a float64
artifact — it is a general law of lossy operations, and it survives
transplantation along two independent axes: more variables (Arm M) and
a different substrate (Arm I).

**Arm M thesis:** lane-carried exactness, the difference calculus, the
fingerprint law, and the landing decomposition lift from univariate to
bivariate (n = 2) with the account gaining *direction* — per-variable
attribution, coupling channels, and a measurable commutator — while
every exactness claim stays exact in ℚ.

**Arm I thesis:** for fixed-width integer and shift operations, the
discarded complement (carry, remainder, shifted-out bits) is exactly
representable, lawful under composition, and verdict-bearing — and at
least one of its laws unifies with an existing float-side law rather
than merely mimicking it.

**Relationship between arms:** independent machinery, shared
meta-thesis. Recommended execution: **two campaigns under one
charter** (§10, ruling #1). Either order is coherent; tradeoffs in §10.

**Strategic placement:** Arm M is upstream infrastructure for
TWO-CURVATURES (curvature = Hessian-class object; the banked seed needs
multivariate accounts to run at full strength). Arm I is the short,
sharp campaign with a unification headline (§I-A) and the project's
best outreach fixture (§I-D). Neither jumps the atlas close queue.

